Over the past few weeks the station has suffered sporadic faults resulting in power cuts in surrounding suburbs. JOHANNESBURG - City Power says its Roosevelt sub station will be refurbished due to ongoing power cuts at the station.Over the past few weeks the station has suffered intermittent faults resulting in power cuts in surrounding suburbs.Acting spokesperson Yumna Sheik says: Because of the old infrastructure we actually have a consolidated infrastructure plan which we are currently busy with. Roosevelt is part of the substations that are going through an upgrade. The upgrade started toward the later part of last year 2016. The value of the upgrade is in the region of R110 million. (Edited by Neo Koza)